  <description><![CDATA[<ul>
<li><span>Ski up to altitudes of </span>3,303 metres</li>
<li>Over 350 kilometres of combined ski area across the Upper Engadine resorts </li>
</ul>
<p>St Moritz has an idyllic location in Switzerlands Engadine valley and is one of the most recognised resorts in the world. The resort itself is split into three villages: <span>Dorf, on the shore of the lake, has the pick of shops, nightlife, and restaurants. This is where our hotels are located. St. Moritz Bad is less than 2 kilometres away - it's quaint and quieter in comparison. Celerina, on the other side of Dorf, has more of an Italian influence and still has its share of hotels and restaurants. All villages have access to the home mountain, Corviglia. </span></p>
<h2>Skiing and snowboarding in St. Moritz</h2>
<p>The three main ski areas are Corviglia<span>, </span>Corvatsch<span> &amp; </span>Diavolezza-Lagalb, all of which offer you something different. they're all linked by the local ski bus, which is included in your lift pass. With more than 155 kilometres of runs close to home at Corviglia, many skiers and snowboarders are happy to remain on the local slopes for the duration of their stay. Others will want to see what other temptations the area's have to offer. Across the valley, Corvatsch is reached by cable cars from Surlej or Furtschellas at either end of Lake Silvaplana, and provides a large area of quite steep terrain. For non-skiers, there’s a wide array of activities including more than 200 kilometres of scenic cross-country tracks and miles of winter walking trails.</p>
<h2>Where to stay in St. Moritz</h2>
<p>We offer a choice of comfortable and stylish hotels in St. Moritz centre. Whether you're looking for modern chic, traditional Engadine or <span>Belle Epoque style during your stay in St. Moritz we've got the hotel for you. Many of our hotels have wellness facilities - so you can relax and unwind after a day in the mountains. </span></p>
<h2>Bars and restaurants in St. Moritz</h2>
<p><span>St Moritz is a gem for the foodies, with an array of restaurants from Michelin-star spots to cosy alpine restaurants, you are truly in for a treat here. </span><span></span><span>It has a sophisticated laid back vibe compared to other Swiss resorts like <a data-udi="umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1}" title="Zermatt">Zermatt</a>, however there are still plenty of bars on and off the mountain to enjoy. The Sky Bar at the <a data-udi="umb://document/990d57a643344020abc9d610d2715f84" href="/{localLink:umb://document/990d57a643344020abc9d610d2715f84}" title="Hotel Monopol">Hotel Monopol</a> is one of our favourite's - you cant beat the views across the lake from here. If you're after live music and a great atmosphere, then the Stübli Bar is a good bet - it's popular with tourists and locals alike. </span></p>
<h2>What's included in an Inghams holiday to St.Moritz </h2>
<p><span>On an Inghams holiday you'll have, flights, rail transfers and accommodation based on a half board or bed and breakfast basis included. We operate a remote rep service in St. Moritz - so you'll have a member of our experienced team based in Switzerland, available to assist you over the phone, should you need anything while you're away. You'll also have the choice to add on optional extras including ski equipment and lift passes - see the 'Ski extras' tab below for more information on these.</span><span></span></p>
<p><span>You might also like:</span></p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/b23ef1df250240c5a3657f721fdb96d0" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/switzerland/graubunden-ski-region/klosters" title="Klosters">Discover Klosters ski holidays</a></p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/a95de5322c984f85bcf0f013c457e8df" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a95de5322c984f85bcf0f013c457e8df}" title="Davos">Discover Davos ski holidays</a></p>
<h2>Short on time but big on adventure?</h2>
<p>Our flexible <a data-udi="umb://document/d137b11ca7414c7b817405b2fd7405b8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d137b11ca7414c7b817405b2fd7405b8}" title="Ski Weekends &amp; Short Breaks to Switzerland">short ski breaks in Switzerland</a> have you covered! Hit the slopes for as long or as short as you like. Design your perfect Swiss ski getaway! Choose your duration, departure day, hotel, and resort. Fly from your preferred airport and customize your trip with extras like ski hire and lift passes.​</p>
<p>​The choice is yours, flexible durations available in 10 resorts and 34 hotels across Switzerland.</p>]]></description>
